<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3838] CLI parameter parser is munging application params</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3838</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If parameters for an application use a single &apos;-&apos; (e.g. -maxtasks) then the CLI argument parser will munge these, and the app gets passed either just the parameter name (e.g. &apos;maxtask&apos;) if the start of the parameter doesn&apos;t match a Flink parameter, or you get two values, with the first value being the part that matched (e.g. &apos;-m&apos;) and the second value being the rest (e.g. &apos;axtasks&apos;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The parser should ignore everything after the jar path parameter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that using --&amp;lt;parameter name&amp;gt; does seem to work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12963181">FLINK-3838</key>
